      • test_empty_group

        public void test_empty_group()
                      throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                             TokenMgrError,
                             ParseException
        Test empty group. The group pattern: 
         {}
        matches any graph (including the empty graph) with one solution that does not bind any variables. For example: 
         SELECT ?x
 WHERE {}
        matches with one solution in which variable x is not bound.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

                                                            throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                                                   TokenMgrError,
                                                                   ParseException
        IN with an arg list in a FILTER. The arg list has a single value. This should be turned into a SameTerm constraint. 
         SELECT ?s where {?s ?p ?o. FILTER (?s IN(?o))}

      • test_simple_triple_pattern_with_IN_filter_variables

        public void test_simple_triple_pattern_with_IN_filter_variables()
                                                         throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                                                TokenMgrError,
                                                                ParseException
        IN with a non-empty arg list in a FILTER. The arguments are expressions rather than constants. This should be turned into a ComputedIN. 
         SELECT ?s where {?s ?p ?o. FILTER (?s IN(?p,?o))}
        Throws:

      • test_simple_triple_pattern_with_IN_filter_constants

        public void test_simple_triple_pattern_with_IN_filter_constants()
                                                         throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                                                TokenMgrError,
                                                                ParseException
        IN with a non-empty arg list in a FILTER. The arguments are expressions rather than constants. This should be turned into an optimized IN using a hash set or binary search. 
         SELECT ?s where {?s ?p ?o. FILTER (?s IN(?p,?o))}
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException
